odal_main_2528852\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jfo1665702963950.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jfo1665702963950.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jfo1665702963950.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jfo1665702963950\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Environment Considerations for Sybase\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<section class=\"section\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d139739e59\">\n                        \n Network Considerations\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__p_d59012e1_d59013e1_d59014e1\">Sybase always uses a network for accessing the server, even if it is on the local machine. Accessing servers on other machines is therefore completely transparent for Uniface. The Sybase <span class=\"ph filepath\">interfaces</span> file manages the server administration. Refer to your Sybase documentation for more information.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__p_d59015e1_d59016e1_d59017e1\">The Uniface Server is supported for those who require it. This also provides transparent network connectivity.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d139739e74\">\n                        \n Permissions\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__p_d59021e1_d59022e1_d59023e1\">For each database a user accesses, the user must have select permission on certain system tables. The SQL Server installation program sets up permissions so that all users can read the necessary system tables by default. However, database owners can control the permissions on the system tables in their own databases.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__p_d59024e1_d59025e1_d59026e1\">The following system tables must be accessible to users:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__li_d26456e1_d26457e1_d26458e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__p_d59027e1_d59028e1_d59029e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">sysobjects</span>\n</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__li_d26459e1_d26460e1_d26461e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__p_d59030e1_d59031e1_d59032e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">sysusers</span>\n</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__li_d26462e1_d26463e1_d26464e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__p_d59033e1_d59034e1_d59035e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">sysdepends</span> (only if Sybase views are used)</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__li_d26465e1_d26466e1_d26467e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__p_d59036e1_d59037e1_d59038e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">syscolumns</span> (only if multi-table views are used which contain segmented fields)</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__li_d26468e1_d26469e1_d26470e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__p_d59039e1_d59040e1_d59041e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">sysalternates</span>\n</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__p_d59042e1_d59043e1_d59044e1\">To use the Load Definitions utility, users must have select permission on the following Sybase system catalogs:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__li_d26471e1_d26472e1_d26473e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__p_d59045e1_d59046e1_d59047e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">sysobjects</span>\n</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__li_d26474e1_d26475e1_d26476e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__p_d59048e1_d59049e1_d59050e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">syscolumns</span>\n</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__li_d26477e1_d26478e1_d26479e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__p_d59051e1_d59052e1_d59053e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">sysindexes</span>\n</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__li_d26480e1_d26481e1_d26482e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jfo1665702963950__p_d59054e1_d59055e1_d59056e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">systypes</span>\n</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528852\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528852\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Environment Considerations for Sybase Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Environment Considerations for Sybase Network Considerations Sybase always uses a network for accessing the server, even if it is on the local machine. Accessing servers on other machines is therefore completely transparent for Uniface. The Sybase interfaces file manages the server administration. Refer to your Sybase documentation for more information. The Uniface Server is supported for those who require it. This also provides transparent network connectivity. Permissions For each database a user accesses, the user must have select permission on certain system tables. The SQL Server installation program sets up permissions so that all users can read the necessary system tables by default. However, database owners can control the permissions on the system tables in their own databases. The following system tables must be accessible to users: sysobjects sysusers sysdepends (only if Sybase views are used) syscolumns (only if multi-table views are used which contain segmented fields) sysalternates To use the Load Definitions utility, users must have select permission on the following Sybase system catalogs: sysobjects syscolumns sysindexes systypes Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}